<!-- Modules -->

<!-- Introduction To Module Manager -->
	<sect2 id="module-introduction">
  		<title>Introduction To The Module Manager</title>
		<para>
		The "module" is the unit of content in GnomeSword, and Sword generally; a Sword module is a resource available for viewing
		in Sword applications.  There are several varieties: Most importantly, Bible texts, as well as dictionaries and lexicons,
		commentaries, and general books, including some which have graphical content (e.g. atlases).  They are installed either
		from a local directory structure (such as a CDROM distribution) or remotely via ftp from a server such as Crosswire, which
		is the home of Sword, and from which all officially Sword-sanctioned modules are available.
		</para>
		<para>
		If you have other Sword applications installed, they will all share the same set of Sword modules that you install through
		the Module Manager.
		</para>
